cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about pre-trained language models for Vietnamese, which is a natural language processing (NLP) task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the performance of the models, which suggests that it could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions named-entity recognition, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR), so cs.IR is also a possible category. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category because the models are based on neural networks.
